    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-sea-bass-with-tarragon-bearnaise-waxy-potatoes-and-tenderstem/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>waxy potatoes </strong>to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film </strong>and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Microwave the potatoes for 6-8 min!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-sea-bass-with-tarragon-bearnaise-waxy-potatoes-and-tenderstem/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>sea bass fillet[s] </strong>dry with kitchen paper and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-sea-bass-with-tarragon-bearnaise-waxy-potatoes-and-tenderstem/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned sea bass fillet[s]</strong>, skin side down and cook for 6 min, then flip the sea bass and cook for 1 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-sea-bass-with-tarragon-bearnaise-waxy-potatoes-and-tenderstem/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the sea bass is cooking, add your<strong> Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a pot with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cover with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-sea-bass-with-tarragon-bearnaise-waxy-potatoes-and-tenderstem/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> to a small heatproof bowl and put in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 10-20 seconds or until just melted</p><p>Once melted, add in your <strong>mayo</strong> with your <strong>parsley & tarragon pesto </strong>and<strong> </strong>whisk until you have a thick sauce</p><p>Add a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tarragon b\u00e9arnaise</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-sea-bass-with-tarragon-bearnaise-waxy-potatoes-and-tenderstem/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-sea-bass-with-tarragon-bearnaise-waxy-potatoes-and-tenderstem/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cooked sea bass </strong>with the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong>, <strong>waxy potatoes </strong>and <strong>tarragon b\u00e9arnaise</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
